revision.text:
'''Weather''' is a game mechanic reflecting atmospheric conditions that affects Pokémon attack values of certain types. It changes every four hours and certain weather conditions can only occur in specific [[Region|regions]]. Weather also restricts the evolution and in-route availability of certain Pokémon.
=Details=
The table below is accurate as of version 0.6.8.
{| class="wikitable" |- ! Weather !! Description !! Type modifier(s) !! RNG weight !! Region |- | Clear || The weather is clear and pleasant. || None || 30 || rowspan = 5 | All |- | Overcast || Clouds fill the skies. || None || 20 |- | Rain || It's rainy and humid. || Water x1.1|| 10 |- | Thunderstorm || The weather is clear and pleasant. || Water x1.1, Electric x1.1 || 5 |- | Sunny || The sunlight is strong. || Fire x1.1, Grass x1.1 || 10 |- | Snow || It's cold and snowing. || Ice x1.05 || 5 || rowspan = 3 | Johto onwards |- | Hail || It's cold and hailing. || Ice x1.1 || 3 |- | Blizzard || A howling blizzard blows. || Ice x1.2, Fire x0.9, Grass x0.9 || 2 |- | Sandstorm || A sandstorm is raging. || Rock x1.1, Ground x1.1, Steel x1.1 || 10 || Hoenn onwards |- | Fog || The fog is deep... || Ghost x1.1 || 10 || Sinnoh |- | Windy || Mysterious strong winds blow. || Flying x1.2, Dragon x1.1 || 1 || None |}
